1. **Analyze and Describe the Main Target Image:**

The main image depicts two structures.

* **Structure 1 (Tower):**  This structure is composed of 9 blocks in 3 layers.
    * **Spatial Relationships:** The central part of the tower has 3 vertical blocks of green (index 3) stacked on top of a yellow (index 5) block. Two orange (index 9) cylindrical blocks form the side supports of this central portion, with one placed on top of the other. The top of the tower is capped with a red triangular block (index 13).  A second red triangular block (index 13) is on the second level. The base of the tower sits on an orange (index 9) block.


* **Structure 2 (Small House):**  This structure is composed of 4 blocks in 2 layers.
    * **Spatial Relationships:**  A blue (index 1) triangular block sits atop a yellow (index 5) rectangular block, which rests on two orange cylindrical blocks (index 9). A red triangular block (index 13) forms the roof.
